  "_meta": {
    "purpose": "Batch 4 of the districts fan-out: full rows for 13 Nassau school districts, mirroring the pilot schema in site/assets/districts.json. Every field carries a source_ref (url, vintage, verified). Fields that cannot be verified from a primary source are OMITTED, never estimated. Do NOT merge blindly: intended to be reconciled into site/assets/districts.json.",
    "batch": 4,
    "built": "2026-07-20",
    "method": "Replicates the L1 pilot method (.claude/scratch/districts-provenance.md): Census B25077 school-district geography, NYSED search_schools.php instid + enrollment.php, OSC iq85-sdzs levy, Nassau GIS REST parcel discovery -> LRV /info cookie -> POST /gstaxes.php for Class-1 school/library rates.",
    "notes": [
      "medianValue uses the SCHOOL-DISTRICT geography directly (preferred), not a place proxy: unified districts = sumlevel 970 (9700000US<geoid>); the two ELEMENTARY districts (Floral Park-Bellerose, Valley Stream 24) = sumlevel 950 (9500000US<geoid>). ACS does not publish B25077 for these under the 970 prefix.",
      "Elementary districts (Floral Park-Bellerose = Sewanhaka CHSD component; Valley Stream 24 = Valley Stream CHSD component): the Nassau LRV school bill shows a SINGLE combined Net School Tax line (elementary + CHSD billed together), not separate elementary and CHSD lines. The recorded schoolRate is that combined rate. Confirmed by the STAR-savings line matching the DTF elementary-district exempt savings to the dollar.",
      "Glen Cove City SD: schoolRate/libraryRate OMITTED. Glen Cove assesses its own roll; the county LRV explicitly returns 'located within the City of Glen Cove' and shows no school tax lines. Same archetype as the Long Beach pilot gap. levy is still available from OSC.",
      "libraryRate is present only where the sampled Class-1 parcel's school bill carries a separate Net Library Tax line. East Rockaway, Malverne, Mineola, North Shore, and the two elementary districts show no such line on the sampled parcel and libraryRate is omitted (library funded off the school bill).",
      "Every parcel with a STAR line independently reproduces the DTF exempt-savings figure to the dollar (Floral Park-Bellerose 752, Malverne 983, North Shore 829, Valley Stream 24 831, Seaford enhanced 3019) - a cross-source validation of the correct district and rate.",
      "STAR fields (starCredit / starExemptSavings / starMaxExemptSavings2026_27) are carried unchanged from the existing verified stub rows in districts.json (DTF, 2026-07-20).",
      "county_leg intentionally omitted (officials lane; re-verify same-day before any politician-facing use).",
      "No FOIL-gated section-467 / exemption-gap figures appear here, per the standing rule."
    ],
    "gaps": [
      "Glen Cove schoolRate + libraryRate: city-roll archetype; needs a City of Glen Cove tax bill / city assessor source.",
      "Separate elementary-vs-CHSD rate split for Floral Park-Bellerose and Valley Stream 24: the county LRV bills them as one combined line, so the split is not separable from this source.",
      "libraryRate for East Rockaway, Malverne, Mineola, North Shore (no school-bill library line on the sampled parcel)."
    ]
  },
